fu.obj

Class LRUCache<T_KEY,T_VALUE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fu.obj.LRUCache<T_KEY,T_VALUE>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PersistentLRUCache

    public class LRUCache<T_KEY,T_VALUE>
extends java.lang.Object
    An LRU cache. It has a predefined maximum size. Additional put then remove 10% of the recently used entries. Recently used means: The last one that has been written or read. Apart from the maximum size - this is a hashtable. It is thread-safe. The class also is able to store null values. As a get would return null if either there was no hit, or a null was explicitly stored, there is a function wasHit that indicates, if the last get was a cache hit.
